What is AWS Lambda?

AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service that lets you run code without provisioning or managing servers.

 You upload your function ‚Üí AWS handles:
‚úî Infrastructure
 ‚úî Scaling
 ‚úî High availability
 ‚úî Patching
 ‚úî Capacity planning

You only pay for execution time, measured in milliseconds.

Lambda can be triggered by over 200+ AWS events (S3 uploads, API calls, EventBridge, SNS, DynamoDB streams, CloudWatch events, etc.), making it perfect for automation.

